** DOM **

1. querySelector.     (mostly)
2. querySelectorAll   (mostly)

3. placeholder , onclick 

4. getElementById
5. getElementsByClassName

6. updating involves - innerHTML 

7. getElementById ,but to get the parent node for deleteing we can use - Element.parentNode; 

8. to add an element - appendChild 
9. to remove an element -removeChild 

10. createElement - to create an element  (used to add ,basically used before append)


